lead_paragraph: An aquarium service technician is part plumber, part veterinarian, and part ringmaster of a world where things aren’t meant to live in harmony.
snippet: An aquarium service technician is part plumber, part veterinarian, and part ringmaster of a world where things aren’t meant to live in harmony....
abstract: Andy Newman Pet City column describes how aquarium service technicians, self-described 'fish guys,' maintain aquatic environments throughout New York City; techs say they are homemade scientists whose job is to help pet owners avert disasters in pricey ecosystems of artificial tanks filled with unlikely combinations of exotic fish and corals.
